<h1>How this data was produced</h1>

<p>All outputs in this repository are generated by a 5-step pipeline that starts from raw FOAA-obtained Flock audit logs and ends with the analysis findings cited in the press release. Each step has its own methodology document and is independently reproducible.</p>

<ol class="methodology-steps">
  <li>
    <strong>Deduplicate raw audit logs</strong><br>
    Merge per-network query rows into unique search sessions. Raw logs (2,007 rows) become 1,572 deduplicated sessions.
    <br><a href="{{ "/methodology/deduplication.html" | url }}">Full methodology →</a>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Normalize shared-network organization names</strong><br>
    Extract state codes, strip common suffixes (PD, SO, etc.), and lowercase agency names from the Flock shared-networks spreadsheet.
    <br><a href="{{ "/methodology/deduplication.html" | url }}">Deduplication methodology →</a>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Classify assist-other-agency searches</strong><br>
    Scan the Reason field for cross-agency language ("assist other", MIAC, MDEA). Flag 107 entries in two categories.
    <br><a href="{{ "/methodology/assist-classification.html" | url }}">Full methodology →</a>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Cross-index against ICE 287(g) participants</strong><br>
    Match normalized SPPD agencies against ICE's official 287(g) list using state-mandatory + Jaccard name similarity ≥ 0.75. Result: 73 matches.
    <br><a href="{{ "/methodology/287g-crossindex.html" | url }}">Full methodology →</a>
  </li>
  <li>
    <strong>Count unique states</strong><br>
    Extract and deduplicate state codes from all 602+ agencies. Result: 44 states.
    <br><a href="{{ "/methodology/state-counting.html" | url }}">State counting methodology →</a>
  </li>
</ol>

<h2>Provenance</h2>

<p>Every input file has a SHA-256 hash recorded in its corresponding methodology document. Every output file is generated by a script committed to the repository. Running <code>./run.sh</code> from a clean clone reproduces all outputs from the original data.</p>